#X text 31 60 Here are other two patches with the cuttof of the filter is set by a decaying envelope but with [adsr~]. Below \, for short notes before the decay time \, we have a quick release of 10ms to match the release of the amplitude envelope \, which is a simple [glide~] object working as a ASR envelope., f 45;
#X text 276 469 Note that now we add some overdrive AFTER THE OUTPUT of the filter \, which is quite different than having it before and distorts the output. This type of subtractive synthesis patch is common in 'ACID' like music. To the right we have a [moog~] object \, whose drive parameter is on the input so you can also include another overdrive to the output!, f 35;
